reviewText: This is something you'd see on Impact Action On Demand. Not the best of his work, but, a good story and message.

OK...bad acting, bad special effects and bad dialog. BUT it was so bad it was good/funny! I first saw this movie when I was probably about 12 and even to someone at that age it was laughable. I haven't seen it in wars but what stands out the most is the crack house!
Its fun to watch how far fetched and low budget this movie is. Its cheesy-ness will always remain a gem in my collection.
